 {"id":"franken_networkx-zzcm7","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: directed component and topological error contracts diverge","description":"The wide parity matrix found strongly_connected_components yields SCCs in a different order from upstream NetworkX on directed fixtures. It also found topological_sort on a cyclic digraph raises HasACycle where upstream raises NetworkXUnfeasible.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T04:58:49.422775Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T04:58:49.422775Z","close_reason":"Fixed: SCC emits in nx sink-first order; topological_sort/generations/lexicographic raise NetworkXUnfeasible (not HasACycle) on cyclic input.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
