+{"id": "franken_networkx-degnbn", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] G.degree(nbunch) raises NodeNotFound on missing nodes \u2014 nx silently skips", "description": "fnx.Graph.degree([0, 99]) raised NodeNotFound(99) instead of yielding only (0, 1) per nx contract (nx uses nbunch_iter to filter). Other nbunch-accepting APIs (edges, subgraph, nbunch_iter) already filtered correctly. Fix: in _WeightAwareDegreeView.__call__, filter iterable nbunches through in-graph check before invoking the Rust raw degree view. Single-node lookups still preserve KeyError/NodeNotFound behavior.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T06:23:54.704823Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: _WeightAwareDegreeView.__call__ now nbunch-filters iterable inputs via (n for n in nbunch if n in self._graph).", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T06:23:54.704823Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T06:23:54.704823Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
